results.name: Number of partitions of n with product of multiplicities of parts equal to 4.
link: Vaclav Kotesovec, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..18694 (terms 0..10000 from Alois P. Heinz)
formula: a(n) ~ c * exp(Pi*sqrt(n/3)) * n^(1/4), where c = 0.0108735520090052... - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 24 2018
maple: b:= proc(n, i, p) option remember; `if`(n=0, `if`(p=1, 1, 0),
mathematica: b[n_, i_, p_] := b[n, i, p] = If[n == 0, If[p == 1, 1, 0], If[i < 1, 0, b[n, i - 1, p] + Sum[If[Mod[p, j] == 0, b[n - i*j, i - 1, p/j], 0], {j, 1, n/i}]]]; a[n_] := b[n, n, 4]; Table[a[n], {n, 0, 70}] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Dec 22 2016, after _Alois P. Heinz_ *)
results.author: _Emeric Deutsch_ and _Alois P. Heinz_, Jan 02 2016
